After my Iceland trip last fall, the hard drive I had been working on failed! Which was devastating considering this was my first international trip since the pandemic and the first vacation with my partner @pete_ohara. 

Generally I’m quick at backing up files, but the hard drive itself was only a couple months old, a recent purchase and a hard lesson to learn. 

Thankfully after months of searching for data recovery experts and using insurance, I was finally able to recover about 97% of the drive 🫶

I’m currently in Peru, but needless to say I’m excited to get back to my work from Iceland 🤍 here’s a couple snaps I had saved on my phone in collaboration with @gocampers 

If you ever find yourself in the same situation, I’ve got your guy!!
.
.
.

Huacachina sunsets are pretty magical to say the least 🧡

Having been in Peru now 2 times, I wasn’t about to leave without taking in a little R&R at this little desert oasis. And while I only had the time to spend one night in this location, I’m really happy to have checked it off the bucket list and watch the sun dip under the horizon deep within the dunes 🐪

To the last day of 2023 🥂

Sometimes I find it difficult to pour every experience and memory into words…mostly because they are my own…lived, breathed, cherished…personal. 2023 amidst its highs and lows was a year I’m incredibly grateful for. One of introspection, growth, and wonderful adventure.

But rather than run though it all, really I just wanted to say hello and to thank those of you that follow and engage with this page. For your friendship and for your support 🤍 

Tomorrow marks a new day, and a new year for us all ✨ An opportunity to start anew in a sense. A door I plan to open like any other…full of love, hope, and gratitude. See you on the other side.
.
